1 L.D. 758
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 AGRICULTURE, CONSERVATION AND FORESTRY
4 Reproduced and distributed under the direction of the Secretary of the Senate.
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 291, L.D. 758, “Resolve, to Update
10 Flood Mapping in the Sandy River Watershed to Federal Emergency Management Agency
11 Standards”
12 Amend the resolve by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'Resolve, to Conduct a Study to Update Flood Hazard Data in the Sandy River
14 Watershed'
15 Amend the resolve by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
16 'Sec. 1. Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry, Maine
17 Geological Survey to conduct Sandy River watershed geomorphic study.
18 Resolved: That, in coordination with the United States Department of Homeland Security,
19 Federal Emergency Management Agency; the Department of Transportation; the
20 Department of Environmental Protection; the Department of Inland Fisheries and Wildlife;
21 the Maine Office of Community Affairs; the Department of Defense, Veterans and
22 Emergency Management, Maine Emergency Management Agency; and other relevant state
23 agencies, the Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry, Bureau of Resource
24 Information and Land Use Planning, Division of Geology, Natural Areas and Coastal
25 Resources, Maine Geological Survey shall contract for a geomorphic study within the
26 Sandy River watershed to update flood hazard data within the watershed. The study must
27 include an assessment of river movement, erosion and sedimentation and the impacts of
28 those factors on flood risk and river health. The study must also provide individuals who
29 reside within the Sandy River watershed and individuals who reside within the watershed
30 of similar river systems with information about flood risks and options to manage those
31 risks. The Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry, in collaboration with
32 relevant state agencies, shall seek funding to support the costs of the study.'
33 Amend the resolve by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
34 section number to read consecutively.
