COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 291, L.D. 758
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment replaces the resolve and changes the title. The amendment directs the
33 Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry, Bureau of Resource Information
44 and Land Use Planning, Division of Geology, Natural Areas and Coastal Resources, Maine
55 Geological Survey, in coordination with the United States Department of Homeland
66 Security, Federal Emergency Management Agency and relevant state agencies, to contract
77 for a geomorphic study within the Sandy River watershed to update flood hazard data
88 within the watershed. The study must include an assessment of river movement, erosion
99 and sedimentation and the impacts of those factors on flood risk and river health and
1100 provide information about flood risks and management options to individuals who reside
1111 within the Sandy River watershed or the watersheds of similar river systems. The
1122 Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry, in collaboration with relevant state
1133 agencies, is required to seek funding to support the costs of the study.
1144 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
1155 (See attached)
